FBIS3-59935 "jptac001___94061" JPRS-TAC-94-001 Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Arms Control 18 January 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA UKRAINE Japan Reportedly To Assist Financing of Nuclear Disarmament LD1712122493 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 0845 GMT 17 Dec 93 LD1712122493 Kiev UNIAN Language: Ukrainian Article Type:BFN [Text] Kiev [no date as receivedd] -- A UNIAN correspondent was informed at the Japanese Embassy in Ukraine that a working meeting of employees of the Foreign Ministries of Japan and Ukraine took place on 16 December about Japan's assistance in eliminating Ukrainian nuclear weapons. According to information of the embassy's secretary, Japan will finance nuclear disarmament of Ukraine, Belarus, Kazakhstan, and Russia irrespective of the assessments of the state's government or the manner of ratification of the START I Treaty by Ukraine. The total sum, which Japan is currently planning to spend on these four states comes to $100 million. But a final decision regarding Ukraine's share has not been adopted yet.
